":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Barrett was born about 1400, in Rougham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with John Whitewell. She died about 1469, in her hometown, at the age of 71."},"et":{"about 1400–about 1469":"umbes 1400–umbes 1469","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1423–1487":"1423–1487","1400–1469":"1400–1469","1469":"1469","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1487":"1487","about 1469":"umbes 1469","about 1400":"umbes 1400","about 1423":"umbes 1423","Rougham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rougham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1400–about 1469":"noin 1400–noin 1469","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1423–1487":"1423–1487","1400–1469":"1400–1469","1469":"1469","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1487":"1487","about 1469":"noin 1469","about 1400":"noin 1400","about 1423":"noin 1423","Rougham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rougham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1400–about 1469":"environ 1400–environ 1469","1400–Male":"1400–Décédé","1423–1487":"1423–1487","1400–1469":"1400–1469","1469":"1469","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1487":"1487","about 1469":"environ 1469","about 1400":"environ 1400","about 1423